nodes.name: Aphrodite
nodes.attribute: Goddess of love, beauty, desire, sex, and pleasure.

nodes.name: Apollo
nodes.attribute: God of music, arts, knowledge, healing, plague, prophecy, poetry, manly beauty, archery, and the sun.

nodes.name: Ares
nodes.attribute: God of war, bloodshed, and violence.

nodes.name: Artemis
nodes.attribute: Virgin goddess of the hunt, wilderness, animals, young girls, childbirth, plague, and the moon.

nodes.name: Athena
nodes.attribute: Goddess of intelligence, skill, peace, warfare, battle strategy, handicrafts, and wisdom.

nodes.name: Demeter
nodes.attribute: Goddess of grain, agriculture and the harvest, growth and nourishment.

nodes.name: Dionysus
nodes.attribute: God of wine, parties and festivals, madness, chaos, drunkenness, drugs, and ecstasy.

nodes.name: Hades
nodes.attribute: King of the underworld and the dead, and god of regret.

nodes.name: Hephaestus
nodes.attribute: Crippled god of fire, metalworking, and crafts.

nodes.name: Hera
nodes.attribute: Queen of the gods and goddess of marriage, women, childbirth, heirs, kings, and empires.

nodes.name: Hermes
nodes.attribute: God of boundaries, travel, communication, trade, language, and writing.

nodes.name: Hestia
nodes.attribute: Virgin goddess of the hearth, home and chastity.

nodes.name: Poseidon
nodes.attribute: God of the sea, rivers, floods, droughts, and earthquakes.

nodes.name: Zeus
nodes.attribute: King and father of the gods, the ruler of Mount Olympus and the god of the sky, weather, thunder, lightning, law, order, and justice.

nodes.name: Aether
nodes.attribute: The god of the upper atmosphere and light.

nodes.name: Ananke
nodes.attribute: The goddess of inevitability, compulsion, and necessity.

nodes.name: Chaos
nodes.attribute: The nothingness from which all else sprang.

nodes.name: Chronos
nodes.attribute: The god of time.

nodes.name: Erebus
nodes.attribute: The god of darkness and shadow.

nodes.name: Eros
nodes.attribute: The god of love and attraction.

nodes.name: Hypnos
nodes.attribute: The personification of sleep.

nodes.name: Nesoi
nodes.attribute: The goddesses of the islands and sea.

nodes.name: Uranus
nodes.attribute: The god of the heavens (Father Sky); father of the Titans.

nodes.name: Gaia
nodes.attribute: Personification of the Earth (Mother Earth); mother of the Titans.

nodes.name: Ourea
nodes.attribute: The gods of mountains.

nodes.name: Phanes
nodes.attribute: The god of procreation in the Orphic tradition.

nodes.name: Pontus
nodes.attribute: The god of the sea, father of the fish and other sea creatures.

nodes.name: Tartarus
nodes.attribute: The god of the deepest, darkest part of the underworld, the Tartarean pit (which is also referred to as Tartarus itself).

nodes.name: Thalassa
nodes.attribute: Personification of the sea and consort of Pontus.

nodes.name: Thanatos
nodes.attribute: God of Death.

nodes.name: Hemera
nodes.attribute: The goddess of day.

nodes.name: Nyx
nodes.attribute: The goddess of night.

nodes.name: Nemesis
nodes.attribute: The goddess of retribution.

nodes.name: Coeus
nodes.attribute: Titan of intellect and the axis of heaven around which the constellations revolved.

nodes.name: Crius
nodes.attribute: The least individualized of the Twelve Titans, he is the father of Astraeus, Pallas, and Perses.

nodes.name: Cronus
nodes.attribute: The leader of the Titans, who overthrew his father Uranus only to be overthrown in turn by his son, Zeus.

nodes.name: Hyperion
nodes.attribute: Titan of light.

nodes.name: Iapetus
nodes.attribute: Titan of mortality and father of Prometheus, Epimetheus, Menoetius, and Atlas.

nodes.name: Mnemosyne
nodes.attribute: Titaness of memory and remembrance, and mother of the Nine Muses.

nodes.name: Oceanus
nodes.attribute: Titan of the all-encircling river Oceans around the earth, the fount of all the Earth's fresh-water.

nodes.name: Phoebe
nodes.attribute: Titaness of the "bright" intellect and prophecy, and consort of Koios.

nodes.name: Rhea
nodes.attribute: Titaness of fertility, motherhood and the mountain wilds.

nodes.name: Tethys
nodes.attribute: Titaness of fresh-water, and the mother of the rivers, springs, streams, fountains, and clouds.

nodes.name: Theia
nodes.attribute: Titaness of sight and the shining light of the clear blue sky.

nodes.name: Themis
nodes.attribute: Titaness of divine law and order.

nodes.name: Asteria
nodes.attribute: Titaness of nocturnal oracles and falling stars.

nodes.name: Astraeus
nodes.attribute: Titan of dusk, stars, and planets, and the art of astrology.

nodes.name: Atlas
nodes.attribute: Titan forced to carry the heavens upon his shoulders by Zeus.

nodes.name: Aura
nodes.attribute: Titaness of the breeze and the fresh, cool air of early morning.

nodes.name: Clymene
nodes.attribute: Titaness of renown, fame, and infamy, and wife of Iapetus.

nodes.name: Dione
nodes.attribute: Titaness of the oracle of Dodona.

nodes.name: Helios
nodes.attribute: Titan of the sun and guardian of oaths.

nodes.name: Selene
nodes.attribute: Titaness of the moon.

nodes.name: Eos
nodes.attribute: Titaness of the dawn.

nodes.name: Epimetheus
nodes.attribute: Titan of afterthought and the father of excuses.

nodes.name: Eurybia
nodes.attribute: Titaness of the mastery of the seas and consort of Krios.

nodes.name: Eurynome
nodes.attribute: Titaness of water-meadows and pasturelands, and mother of the three Charites by Zeus.

nodes.name: Lelantos
nodes.attribute: Titan of air and the hunter's skill of stalking prey.

nodes.name: Leto
nodes.attribute: Titaness of motherhood and mother of the twin Olympians, Artemis and Apollo.

nodes.name: Menoetius
nodes.attribute: Titan of violent anger, rash action, and human mortality.

nodes.name: Metis
nodes.attribute: Titaness of good counsel, advice, planning, cunning, craftiness, and wisdom.

nodes.name: Ophion
nodes.attribute: An elder Titan, in some versions of the myth he ruled the Earth with his consort Eurynome before Cronus overthrew him.

nodes.name: Pallas
nodes.attribute: Titan of warcraft.

nodes.name: Perses
nodes.attribute: Titan of destruction.

nodes.name: Prometheus
nodes.attribute: Titan of forethought and crafty counsel, and creator of mankind.

nodes.name: Styx
nodes.attribute: Titaness of the Underworld river Styx and personification of hatred.
